Beneficiary Id The unique CCW identifier for a beneficiary. The CCW assigns a unique beneficiary identification number to each individual who receives Medicare and/or Medicaid and uses that number to identify an individual’s records in all CCW data files. This number does not change during a beneficiary’s lifetime, and CCW uses each number only once. The BENE_ID is specific to the CCW and is not applicable to any other identification system or data source. PDECarrierInpatientOutpatientHHADMEHospiceSNF AB2D, BB2, BCDA, BFD, DPC, SyntheticData CLAIM bene_id BIGINT 8 beneficiaryId BENE_ID R4 ExplanationOfBenefit patient Patient/+beneficiaryId This field provides a reference to the Patient endpoint FHIR Resource so that this beneficiaries patient data can be pulled down using the reference id (beneficiaryId). The value will look something like this: 'Patient/123456'. patient.reference.substring(8,50)

Claim Disposition Code Code indicating the disposition or outcome of the processing of the claim record. In the source CMS National Claims History (NCH), claims are transactional records, and several iterations of the claim may exist (e.g., original claim, an edited/updated version — which also cancels the original claim, etc.). The final reconciled version of the claim is contained in CCW-produced data files, unless otherwise requested. For final claims (at least those that are final at the time of the data file), this value will always be '01'. Operating Indirect Medical Education Amount This is one component of the total amount that is payable on PPS claims, and reflects the IME (indirect medical education) payments for operating expenses (such as labor) for the claim. Inpatient BB2, BCDA, BFD, DPC, SyntheticData CLAIM ime_op_clm_val_amt NUM 12 indirectMedicalEducationAmount IME_OP_CLM_VAL_AMT CCLF1.CLM_OPRTNL_IME_AMT R4 ExplanationOfBenefit extension[N].valueMoney.value
extension[N].url = 'https://bluebutton.cms.gov/resources/variables/ime_op_clm_val_amt'
eob.extension[N].valueMoney.currency = 'USD'
 extension.where(url = 'https://bluebutton.cms.gov/resources/variables/ime_op_clm_val_amt').valueMoney.value
Low Income Cost Sharing Subsidy Amount This is the amount of cost sharing for the drug that was paid by the Part D low-income subsidy (LICS). This field contains plan-reported amounts per drug event; CMS uses this information to reconcile the prospective payments it makes to Part D plans for expected low-income cost sharing with the actual amounts incurred by the plans. Beneficiary Id The unique CCW identifier for a beneficiary. The CCW assigns a unique beneficiary identification number to each individual who receives Medicare and/or Medicaid and uses that number to identify an individual’s records in all CCW data files. This number does not change during a beneficiary’s lifetime, and CCW uses each number only once. The BENE_ID is specific to the CCW and is not applicable to any other identification system or data source. Beneficiary Id The unique CCW identifier for a beneficiary. The CCW assigns a unique beneficiary identification number to each individual who receives Medicare and/or Medicaid and uses that number to identify an individual’s records in all CCW data files. This number does not change during a beneficiary’s lifetime, and CCW uses each number only once. The BENE_ID is specific to the CCW and is not applicable to any other identification system or data source. Part-APart-BPart-CPart-D BB2, BFD, DPC, SyntheticData BENEFICIARIES bene_id BIGINT 8 beneficiaryId BENE_ID R4 Coverage beneficiary.reference coverage.beneficiary = 'Patient/beneficiaryId' (ie. 'Patient/555888', 'Patient/7889873) The coverage.beneficiary is a reference to another FHIR Resource, Patient along with the beneficiaryId used to gather the data for that resource.
Coverage Resource ID Each resource has an id element which contains the 'logical id' of the resource assigned by the server responsible for storing it. Part-APart-BPart-CPart-D BB2, BFD, DPC, SyntheticData BENEFICIARIES bene_id BIGINT 8 beneficiaryId BENE_ID R4 Coverage id coverage.id = 'medicare coverage part-beneficiaryId' (ie. 'part-a-555888', 'part-b-7889873') id
